Controls for swimming pools or spas mounted within 5 feet of the inside walls of the pool or spa, and control panels intended for use with equipment for water-play fountains, water-play areas, and fountains with water in common with swimming pools, including control panels containing swimming pool transformers, or that supply power to equipment in contact with water for such areas, such as submersible pumps, wet-niche or no-niche lighting fixtures, heaters, covers, chlorinators, and timers. See L80. Such equipment is evaluated to UL1563, are covered under category ?Controls? (WAWU) and are intended to be installed in accordance with Article 680 of the National Electrical Code;

Control equipment intended to supply automatic illumination, power, or both, to critical areas and equipment essential to safety of human life, including emergency lighting and power equipment. Such equipment is evaluated to the requirements contained in UL924, are covered under category ?Emergency Lighting and Power Equipment? (FTBR) and intended for installation in accordance with Article 700 of the National Electrical Code;

Fire alarm equipment, (including releasing equipment control units, and smoke control system equipment) and control panels containing electric control units for use in fire-protective signaling systems, or containing or having connections to smoke detectors, fire alarms and central station alarms, see L68. Such equipment or assemblies of equipment are evaluated to the requirements in UL864 and covered under ?Control Units, Releasing Devices? (SYZV), ?Control Units, System? (UOJZ), or ?Smoke Control System Equipment?(UUKL;

Gas or vapor detection equipment intended for connection to emergency alarm equipment, and emergency alarm control equipment containing or having connections to sensors or initiating devices to monitor, detect harmful concentrations of a gas or vapor (such as carbon monoxide (CO), carbon dioxide (CO2), or refrigerants) and/or activate emergency alarm equipment for life safety evacuation purposes, see L68. Such equipment or assemblies of equipment containing these devices is evaluated to UL2075 and covered under category ?Gas and Vapor Detectors and Sensors? (FTAM), or evaluated to UL2017 and covered under the category ?Emergency Alarm System Control Units? (FSZI) or ?Emergency Alarm System Accessories? (FSYE);

Termination boxes or enclosed assemblies consisting only of lengths of bus bars, terminal strips, or terminal blocks with provisions for wire connectors to accommodate conductors of power or distribution circuits. Such equipment is evaluated to the requirements in UL1773 and are covered under the category ?Termination Boxes? (XCKT);

Portable power distribution equipment, (consisting of plug and receptacle connections for input and outputs, power distribution only, no control circuit) for construction sites, theaters, motion picture and television studios, carnivals, circuses, fairs and exhibition halls. Such equipment is evaluated to the requirements in UL1640 and are covered under the category ?Portable Power Distribution Units and Devices? (QPSH) or ?Portable Power Distribution Panels? (QPSM) and are intended for installation in accordance with Articles 518, 520, 525, 530 or 590 of the National Electrical Code;

The controlled equipment supplied from an industrial control panel, such as heaters, luminaries, motors, pumps, machines, robots, air conditioners, or other utilization equipment (except for devices covered by Section 26 and Section 27 of the Standard that serve to condition air within the control panel itself or illumination of the interior of the control panel for servicing purposes);

Motor control centers, including motor control center sections, motor control center units, or equipment mounted within motor control centers, which are constructed in one or more freestanding enclosed sections that are supplied with horizontal bus bars that serves as power connection between adjacent sections and having means to accommodate one or more plug-in or bolt-in motor control center units that are for control of motor loads. Such equipment is evaluated to the requirements contained in UL845 and are covered under the category "Motor Control Centers" (NJAV);

Dead-front switchboards or equipment mounted within dead-front switchboards, which are constructed in one or more freestanding enclosed sections that predominantly contain bus bars and circuit breakers for control of electric power and lighting circuits. Such equipment is evaluated to the requirements contained in UL891, are covered under the category "Switchboards, Dead-Front" (WEVZ), and are intended for installation in accordance with Article 408 of the National Electrical Code; Control units for utility interactive systems (including distributed generation power systems, static converters and inverters for independent power systems, and photovoltaic power units);

Control units for utility interactive systems (including distributed generation power systems, static converters and inverters for independent power systems (such as generators and fuel cells), and photovoltaic power units) and associated control devices and circuits that direct the operation of utility interactive systems. Such equipment is evaluated to the requirements in UL1741 and are covered under the categories of AC Modules (QHYZ), Distributed Resource Power Systems (QIJL) or Static Inverters and Converters for Use in Independent Power Systems (QIKH);

Enclosures for communications equipment, including enclosure and rack systems, and power distribution centers, consisting of components, (such as switches, fuses, circuit breakers, power supplies, environmental control equipment such as fans, heaters, air conditioners or heat exchangers) to supply power, heat, cooling or otherwise support information technology (IT), telecommunications equipment, or audio/video equipment that is factory or field installed into open mounting panel or rack space. Such equipment is covered under the category "Information Technology and Communications Equipment Cabinet, Enclosure, and Rack Systems" (NWIN) or "Power Distribution Centers for Communication Equipment" (QPQY);

